  "base_path": "/report-red-diesel-used-on-public-roads",
  "content_id": "132d5c59-1d0f-43f9-a512-8b5591bba615",
  "description": "Report someone to HMRC if you think they're using red diesel when driving on public roads without a licence",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Report someone to HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) if they’re using <a href=\"/government/publications/excise-notice-75-fuel-for-road-vehicles/excise-notice-75-fuel-for-road-vehicles#can-i-use-rebated-heavy-oils-as-fuel-in-a-road-vehicle\">red diesel</a> on public roads.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It’s illegal to use red diesel on public roads. You can report it to the <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> <a href=\"/government/organisations/hm-revenue-customs/contact/customs-excise-and-vat-fraud-reporting\">Fraud Hotline</a>.</p>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
